   <taskbody>
      <context class="- topic/section task/context ">
         <p class="- topic/p ">Follow this procedure to heat up the melter and light the floor burners:</p>
      </context>
      <steps class="- topic/ol task/steps ">
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Select primary gas and oxygen SSOVs.</cmd>
         </step>
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Once the top thermocouple readings exceed 750 °C (1382 °F), press the Acknowledge
               button on the Melter HMI Safety tab.</cmd>
            <info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info ">
               <ul id="ul_by5_yzt_2dc" class="- topic/ul ">
                  <li class="- topic/li ">The Auto Ignition Top Temperature indicators will turn green.</li>
               </ul>
               <p class="- topic/p ">
                  <fig id="fig_khs_lb5_2dc" class="- topic/fig ">
                     <image href="media/image1.png"
                            placement="break"
                            id="image_qjd_mb5_2dc"
                            align="center"
                            class="- topic/image "/>
                  </fig>
               </p>
            </info>
         </step>
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Verify that the gas and oxygen SSOVs are open.</cmd>
         </step>
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Once the top thermocouple readings exceed 800 °C (1472 °F), use the switches on the
               Melter Combustion Skids to light floor burners.</cmd>
            <info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info ">
               <ul id="ul_wdj_d15_2dc" class="- topic/ul ">
                  <li class="- topic/li ">Start with burner 1.</li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">Turn the switch to the START position.</li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">If the burner has successfully lit, the light above the switch will be
                     on.</li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">Turn the switch to the on position.</li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">If the light doesn’t turn on, turn the switch back to OFF. Inspect the SSOVs
                     for issues and repeat the ignition attempt.</li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">Wait for 30 seconds before lighting the next burner.</li>
               </ul>
               <note id="note_yg3_215_2dc" class="- topic/note ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">Do not light burners 2, 3, and 4 until after the heat-up burner is removed (in
                     step 10).</p>
               </note>
               <p class="- topic/p ">
                  <fig id="fig_zhb_3b5_2dc" class="- topic/fig ">
                     <image href="media/image2.png"
                            id="image_sql_3b5_2dc"
                            placement="inline"
                            class="- topic/image "/>
                  </fig>
               </p>
            </info>
         </step>
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">In DFC, go to the Melter H3F screen and click the H3F Melter Energy from the
               dropdown menu.</cmd>
            <info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info ">
               <ul id="ul_pzg_g15_2dc" class="- topic/ul ">
                  <li class="- topic/li ">Click the Main Burners Startup tab.</li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">Check the Burner Bypass boxes for burners that have not been started yet.</li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">Click the Main Burners to Normal Operation button.</li>
               </ul>
               <note id="note_cbf_h15_2dc" class="- topic/note ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">If the Normal Operation button is not functional, lower the Main Burner Ramping
                     Target Temperature setpoint below the current melter temperature.</p>
               </note>
               <p class="- topic/p ">
                  <fig id="fig_tlb_kb5_2dc" class="- topic/fig ">
                     <image href="media/image3.png"
                            placement="break"
                            id="image_hmn_kb5_2dc"
                            align="center"
                            class="- topic/image "/>
                  </fig>
               </p>
            </info>
         </step>
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Click the Melter Energy (BRN 1-15) and Melter Energy (BRN 16-24) tabs.</cmd>
            <info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info ">
               <ul id="ul_hpw_315_2dc" class="- topic/ul ">
                  <li class="- topic/li ">Set the burners that are running to Remote mode.</li>
               </ul>
               <p class="- topic/p ">
                  <fig id="fig_ayt_gb5_2dc" class="- topic/fig ">
                     <image href="media/image4.png"
                            placement="break"
                            id="image_n3d_hb5_2dc"
                            align="center"
                            class="- topic/image "/>
                  </fig>
               </p>
            </info>
         </step>
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Increase the gas flow to each burner until the melter temperature reaches 875
               °C</cmd>
            <info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info ">
               <p class="- topic/p ">
                  <fig id="fig_r4h_2b5_2dc" class="- topic/fig ">
                     <image href="media/image5.png"
                            placement="break"
                            id="image_t3t_2b5_2dc"
                            align="center"
                            class="- topic/image "/>
                  </fig>
               </p>
            </info>
         </step>
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Once the melter temperature is at or above 875 °C (1607 °F), turn off the heat-up
               burner. </cmd>
            <info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info ">
               <ul id="ul_b3q_k15_2dc" class="- topic/ul ">
                  <li class="- topic/li ">Go to the heat-up skid.</li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">Press the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Brenner Aus </b>button.</li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">Wait 10 seconds and press the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Ventilator Aus</b> button.</li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">Lock out the heat-up skid gas supply.</li>
               </ul>
               <p class="- topic/p ">
                  <fig id="fig_n51_db5_2dc" class="- topic/fig ">
                     <image href="media/image6.png"
                            placement="break"
                            id="image_cnj_db5_2dc"
                            align="center"
                            class="- topic/image "/>
                  </fig>
               </p>
            </info>
         </step>
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <note id="note_nnb_n15_2dc" class="- topic/note "/>
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Remove the heat-up burner.</cmd>
            <info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info ">
               <ul id="ul_udm_415_2dc" class="- topic/ul ">
                  <li class="- topic/li ">Verify that the heat-up burner door jackbolts are completely flush with the
                     inner surface of the door.</li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">Close the heat-up burner door and secure the yellow clamps around the
                     perimeter.</li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">Set the heat-up burner down so it is not contacting any part of the moving
                     structure.</li>
               </ul>
               <p class="- topic/p ">
                  <fig id="fig_pwh_w15_2dc" class="- topic/fig ">
                     <image href="media/image8.png"
                            placement="break"
                            id="image_p4w_w15_2dc"
                            align="center"
                            class="- topic/image "/>
                  </fig>
               </p>
            </info>
         </step>
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Uncheck the Burner Bypass boxes for burners 2, 3, and 4.</cmd>
            <info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info ">
               <ul id="ul_b1f_q15_2dc" class="- topic/ul ">
                  <li class="- topic/li ">Turn on burners 2, 3, and 4.</li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">Set all burners to <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Normal Operation</b> and <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Automatic Remote</b>.</li>
               </ul>
               <p class="- topic/p ">
                  <fig id="fig_rxv_t15_2dc" class="- topic/fig ">
                     <image href="media/image9.png"
                            placement="break"
                            id="image_t12_v15_2dc"
                            align="center"
                            class="- topic/image "/>
                  </fig>
               </p>
            </info>
         </step>
      </steps>
